</taxonomicNameLabel>
, lateral view. 7. paratype male; 8–9. paratype female. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="0FB56AF7FFFE335918FAFBB59814FDDD" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4710397CFFFE335918FAFBB59814FDDD" blockId="4.[151,1436,1125,1360]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="75DBE56EFFFE335918FAFBB59A28FD01" bold="true" box="[199,334,1125,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the late Dr. Judson Linsley Gressitt (
<number id="F1672B5BFFFE33591B40FBB69898FD01" box="[893,1022,1126,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" value="1948.0" valueMax="1982.0" valueMin="1914.0">
<date id="33111FBCFFFE33591B40FBB69898FD01" box="[893,1022,1126,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" value="1914" valueMax="1982">1914–1982</date>
</number>
) for his contribution to the studies of longicorn beetles from the Malay Archipelago and South Pacific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
